"Abstract The objective of this investigation into computer crime, commissioned by the Dutch “Platform Computercriminaliteit” (a committee on computer crime, consisting of both governmental and business representatives) and conducted between October 1989 and September 1990, was to gain an insight into the extent and types of computer crime, into the factors which influence the willingness to report instances to the police, and the legal possibilities and limitations of the fight against computer crime. This report describes the results of the investigation."
